fields.name: Moon Gateway
fields.description: The Lunar Gateway, officially named the Lunar Orbital Platform – Gateway (LOP-G), is a project to build a space station in lunar orbit intended to serve as a solar-powered communications hub, science laboratory, short-term habitation module, and holding area for rovers and other robots.

fields.name: Starship
fields.description: The Starship is a fully reusable second stage and space vehicle being privately developed by the private company SpaceX. It is being designed to be a long-duration cargo- and passenger-carrying spacecraft.

fields.name: James Webb Telescope
fields.description: The James Webb Space Telescope (JWST) is a space telescope that is planned to be the successor to the Hubble Space Telescope.The JWST will provide greatly improved resolution and sensitivity over the Hubble, and will enable a broad range of investigations across the fields of astronomy and cosmology, including observing some of the most distant events and objects in the universe, such as the formation of the first galaxies

fields.name: Starlink Sattelite Constellation
fields.description: Starlink is a satellite constellation development project underway by American company SpaceX, to develop a low-cost, high-performance satellite bus and requisite customer ground transceivers to implement a new space-based Internet communication system.

fields.name: Crew Dragon
fields.description: Dragon 2 or Crew Dragon is a reusable spacecraft developed and manufactured by U.S. aerospace manufacturer SpaceX, intended as the successor to the Dragon cargo spacecraft. The spacecraft launches atop a Falcon 9 Block 5 rocket and returns via ocean splashdown.

fields.name: Tesla Full Autopilot
fields.description: Tesla Autopilot is an advanced driver-assistance system feature offered by Tesla that has lane centering, adaptive cruise control, self-parking, the ability to automatically change lanes, and the ability to summon the car to and from a garage or parking spot.

fields.name: Space Launch System (SLS)
fields.description: The Space Launch System is a US super heavy-lift expendable launch vehicle, which is under development as of August 2019. It is the primary launch vehicle of NASA's deep space exploration plans, including the planned crewed lunar flights of the Artemis program and a possible follow-on human mission to Mars.

fields.name: New Shepard
fields.description: New Shepard is a vertical-takeoff, vertical-landing, human-rated suborbital rocket that is being developed by Blue Origin as a commercial system for suborbital space tourism.

fields.summary: Solve security issue with the remote storage
fields.description: The problem here is that when using third-party file sharing services, the data is typically taken outside of the company’s IT environment, and that means that the data’s privacy settings are beyond the control of the enterprise.  The best way to avoid such a risk is by ensuring you’re your provider encrypts your files during storage, as well as transit, within a range of 128 to 256-bit.
